
[1]sable

   SABLE, n.

   1. A small animal of the weasel kind, the mustela zibelina, found in
   the northern latitudes of America and Asia. It resembles the martin,
   but has a longer head and ears. Its hair is cinereous, but black at the
   tips. This animal burrows in the earth or under trees; in winter and
   summer subsisting on small animals, and in autumn on berries. The fur
   is very valuable.

   2. The fur of the sable.
